<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1642154-caryn"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1224607613i/1642154._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1642154-caryn">Caryn</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I would say no. This is straight up erotica. Also, this book is in the middle of a series, which is not a great place to start. If you are looking for<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I would say no. This is straight up erotica. Also, this book is in the middle of a series, which is not a great place to start. If you are looking for a great paranormal read, I would recommend _The Chronicles of Nick_ by Sherrilyn Kenyon. She also writes paranormal erotica, but this is a YA spinoff. The first book is _Infinity_ and I couldn't put it down. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
